      <Note Title="Vulnerability Description" Type="General" Ordinal="1" xml:lang="en">Mozilla Firefox before 44.0.2 does not properly restrict the interaction between Service Workers and plugins, which allows remote attackers to bypass the Same Origin Policy via a crafted web site that triggers spoofed responses to requests that use NPAPI, as demonstrated by a request for a crossdomain.xml file.</Note>
    </Notes>
